column5: how deep does this lake get? what fish species are there i know there is walleye bass but is there muskie just wondering somebody i know might be looking at cottage on the lake.
All i gotta say is watch the the rock Schoals i was there last sat and right out of the water again almost ripped my lower end right off. THe boat launch is really shallow too Not too deep at all
lots of interesting structure, I've only ever fished the south end and it has kept me pretty busy. Pretty good for smallies and pickerel, muskies are a bit scrawny but a few decent ones.

Yep. Really rocky. I lost a few props there. Used to be good Musky fishing but I haven't seen many lately. Maybe I'll give it a shot this fall. There are tons of smallies, some largies and some pickerel. Lake is pretty deep, mostly 20 feet but some places hit close to 30.
